file path: CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
content: # Code of Conduct

This code of conduct outlines the expected behavior for all contributors to this project. By participating in this project, you agree to abide by this code of conduct.

## Be respectful

Treat other contributors with respect, even if you disagree with them. Avoid personal attacks, insults, and other forms of harassment.

## Be constructive

When providing feedback, focus on the issue at hand and avoid personal attacks. Be specific and provide examples to support your claims.

## Be open to feedback

Be willing to accept feedback from others, even if it is critical. Use feedback to improve your contributions and the project as a whole.

## Be collaborative

Work together to achieve the project goals. Be willing to share your ideas and collaborate with others.

## Be mindful of your language

Be mindful of the language you use in your contributions. Avoid using offensive or discriminatory language.

## Consequences of Unacceptable Behavior

Unacceptable behavior will not be tolerated. If you are found to be violating this code of conduct, you may be:

* Warned
* Suspended from the project
* Banned from the project

## Reporting Unacceptable Behavior

If you witness or experience unacceptable behavior, please report it to the project maintainers.

## Additional Terms

In addition to the general code of conduct, the following terms apply to contributors to this project:

* You must not modify the following files: LICENSE, CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md, and SECURITY.md.
* You must not use the software for any commercial purposes.
* You must not use the software to create any products or services that are harmful or illegal.
* You must not use the software to create any products or services that violate the terms of service of the Curse proxy API.

By contributing to this project, you agree to abide by these terms.

This code of conduct is based on the Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct.